# Banking Security Scanner Platform

This project runs one Next.js frontend, one Node.js orchestration backend, and four FastAPI scanner services.

## Services And Ports

| Service | Folder | Port | Health URL |
| --- | --- | ---: | --- |
| Frontend | `frontend` | `3000` | `http://127.0.0.1:3000` |
| Main backend | `main-backend` | `5000` | `http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/health` |
| Dependency scanner | `dependency-Scanner` | `8001` | `http://127.0.0.1:8001/health` |
| Config scanner | `config-scanner` | `8002` | `http://127.0.0.1:8002/health` |
| Secret scanner | `secret-scanner` | `8003` | `http://127.0.0.1:8003/health` |
| Cipher scanner | `pre-cipher scanner` | `8004` | `http://127.0.0.1:8004/health` |

## Start Everything From Root

Run this from the project root:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2"
.\start-all.cmd -Restart
```

This starts all services in the background and writes logs into:

```text
logs
```

Open the app at:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:3000
```

If you prefer PowerShell directly:

```powershell
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\start-all.ps1 -Restart
```

## Stop Everything From Root

Run:

```powershell
.\stop-all.cmd
```

Or:

```powershell
powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\stop-all.ps1
```

This stops services listening on:

```text
3000, 5000, 8001, 8002, 8003, 8004
```

## Start A Single Service

Open a terminal in the service folder and run its start script.

Dependency scanner:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2\dependency-Scanner"
.\start.cmd
```

Config scanner:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2\config-scanner"
.\start.cmd
```

Secret scanner:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2\secret-scanner"
.\start.cmd
```

Cipher scanner:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2\pre-cipher scanner"
.\start.cmd
```

Main backend:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2\main-backend"
.\start.cmd
```

Frontend:

```powershell
cd "C:\Users\hp\OneDrive\Desktop\open_source\uco-hakethon-s2\frontend"
cmd /c node_modules\.bin\next.cmd dev --webpack -H 127.0.0.1
```

## Stop A Single Service

Stop by port.

Frontend:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }
```

Main backend:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 5000 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }
```

Dependency scanner:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8001 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }
```

Config scanner:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8002 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }
```

Secret scanner:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8003 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }
```

Cipher scanner:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8004 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force }
```

## Logs

When using `start-all`, logs are written here:

```text
logs\dependency-scanner.out.log
logs\dependency-scanner.err.log
logs\config-scanner.out.log
logs\config-scanner.err.log
logs\secret-scanner.out.log
logs\secret-scanner.err.log
logs\cipher-scanner.out.log
logs\cipher-scanner.err.log
logs\main-backend.out.log
logs\main-backend.err.log
logs\frontend.out.log
logs\frontend.err.log
```

## Common Fixes

If `/api/cipher-scans` returns `404`, restart the main backend:

```powershell
.\start-all.cmd -Restart
```

If a scan fails with `ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:8001`, `8002`, `8003`, or `8004`, that scanner service is not running. Start everything again:

```powershell
.\start-all.cmd -Restart
```
